Can suppress from display to user
If set to true, it means that the system displaying the form (or the individual encoding the form for data capture) can choose to omit the question from display to the user.

Some "complex" questionnaires may have questions which are "non-essential" and can be safely skipped without a need for the user to even see them. This is distinct from questions that don't need to be answered, but which must be shown to the user and the user must consciously choose to skip.
If a group or question that contains other groups or questions is marked as "optional", all of its contents are automatically also treated as optional.
